underwriter /ˈʌndəˌraɪtə/

1. N-COUNT An underwriter is someone whose job involves agreeing to provide money for a particular activity or to pay for any losses. 资助人; 担保人 [商业] 

例： If the market will not buy the shares, the underwriter buys them. 如果市场不买这些股票，包销商就会买。 

2. N-COUNT An underwriter is someone whose job is to judge the risks involved in certain activities and decide how much to charge for insurance. 核保人 [商业] 

例： AIG is an organization of insurance underwriters. 美国国际集团是一家保险核保人机构。

</div>

